text: The municipality is located in Krapina-Zagorje County in northern Croatia Hum na Sutli is a municipality in the Krapina-Zagorje County of Croatia. According to the 2011 census, there are 5,060 inhabitants in the municipality, the absolute majority of which are Croats. ==References== Category:Populated places in Krapina-Zagorje County Category:Municipalities of Croatia
title: Hum na Sutli
